HEADWORD: Synoecious
<hw>Syn*oe"cious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>syn-</ets> + Gr. <?/ house.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having
stamens and pistil in the same head, or, in mosses, having antheridia
and archegonia on the same receptacle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

